
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `msguniq` baraye hazf payam-haye tekrar shode dar file-haye tarjome (.po) estefade mishavad. In dastoor komak mikonad ta file-haye tarjome-ye shoma moratabtar va kam-hajmtar bashand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `msguniq input.po`  --> 📄 File voroodi ra moratab va tekrarat ra hazf mikonad.
    🔹 `msguniq -o output.po input.po` --> 📤 Natije ra dar yek file jadid zakhire mikonad.
    🔹 `msguniq --keep-first input.po` --> 🥇 Avalin version har payam tekrar shode ra negah midarad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ msguniq my_translation.po

    🔹 Payam-haye tekrar shode az file `my_translation.po` hazf mishavand va file asli taghir mikonad.

    $ msguniq -o cleaned_translation.po my_translation.po

    🔹 Payam-haye tekrar shode az `my_translation.po` hazf shode va dar file `cleaned_translation.po` zakhire mishavand. File asli taghir nemikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ msguniq --keep-first input.po

    🔹 Agar chand payam moshabeh vojood dashte bashad, avalin payam negah dashte mishavad va baghie hazf mishavand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `msguniq` command is used to remove duplicate messages from translation files (.po). This helps to keep your translation files clean and smaller in size.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `msguniq input.po` --> 📄 Sorts the input file and removes duplicates.
    🔹 `msguniq -o output.po input.po` --> 📤 Saves the output to a new file.
    🔹 `msguniq --keep-first input.po` --> 🥇 Keeps the first occurrence of each duplicate message.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ msguniq my_translation.po

    🔹 Removes duplicate messages from the `my_translation.po` file, modifying the original file.

    $ msguniq -o cleaned_translation.po my_translation.po

    🔹 Removes duplicate messages from `my_translation.po` and saves the result to the `cleaned_translation.po` file. The original file remains unchanged.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ msguniq --keep-first input.po

    🔹 If there are multiple identical messages, the first message is kept, and the others are removed.
